    "body": "AI-assisted: Codex\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\nLSP error responses implicitly rely on a custom `__tostring` function (`vim.lsp.rpc.format_rpc_error`) for formatting. This causes errors that are not created via `vim.lsp.rpc.error` to behave inconsistently with those that are.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, we usually use `log.error` to print these errors, which uses `vim.inspect` under the hood, so the custom `__tostring`  provides little benefit.\r\n\r\nThis increases the difficulty of refactoring the code, as it tightly couples RPC error handling with the LSP. #38525\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nConvert every potential `__tostring` call to an explicit one. Since we don't describe this behavior in the documentation, this should not be a breaking change.      ",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-02T12:53:30Z",
